HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 1139
By Parkinson
A RESOLUTION to commend Pedro Cabrera Acuna for
exemplary service as a legislative intern.
WHEREAS, each legislative session, this General Assembly is pleased to recognize
certain persons who have committed themselves, through their adroit service, to the betterment
of the legislative process; and
WHEREAS, Pedro Cabrera Acuna is one such individual, who has distinguished himself
in his role as a legislative intern for Representative Antonio Parkinson; Mr. Acuna's work has
resulted in innumerable benefits for the legislators he assisted and the General Assembly as a
whole; and
WHEREAS, a native of Tucson, Arizona, Mr. Acuna is married to Angelia Maria Cabrera
Acuna and the father of Keanu Kai Cabrera Acuna and Logan James Cabrera Acuna; and
WHEREAS, Pedro Cabrera Acuna is serving in his ninth year as a sergeant in the U.S.
Army, having initially served as a watercraft operator and later as a respiratory therapist; and
WHEREAS, a senior at Austin Peay State University (APSU), where he is highly
regarded by his peers, Mr. Acuna has achieved remarkable academic success while
participating in the APSU ROTC program and earning a Bachelor of Arts degree in Universities
Studies with a minor in Political Science and Military Science; and
WHEREAS, following graduation, he plans to earn his commission as a U.S. Army
Infantry Officer and continue serving the U.S. Army, reaching the rank of general, and retiring,
knowing that he served honorably; and
WHEREAS, eager to familiarize himself with the myriad aspects and complexities of
Tennessee State government and to further his studies, Pedro Cabrera Acuna brought his many
HJR1139
015815
